	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jun 12th 5:41 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.60]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you have questions about charm kiting take a look.<br><br>We do know that our charm has been nerfed so reagro dosent happen automatically. So id suggest a hotkey is set up for (target nearest enimy and pet attack)<br><br>If you choose to charm kite do not try to kill the other mob meanwhile your charmed mob beats on it. If you do that and charm breaks as you make the final blow, the pc/npc who have made most damage gets the kill (that will be the mob). <br><br>The first of the 2 mobs you kill will most likely give you 1/2 xp since your pet dealth more damage than you. The 2nd will give full xp cuz damage dealth by the other npc is wipe due to its death.<br><br>If you see your charmed mob is getting beaten up by the other..just switch mob to charm when 1 starts to flee.<br><br>Do not switch charm on mobs unless one is fleeing.<br>Charm creates alot of agro. So if you charm on and then charm the other you will have one running after you (non charmed) and the charmed one running beating on the non-charmed (its easier if they beat on each other)<br><br>My hotkey setup for charmkiting would be as follows<br><br>1-2 Melee slot 1 and 2<br>3-4 Two inventory slots <br>5- Macro button with target nearest npc and pet attack<br>6-10 song slots<br><br>I would use this songs in slots<br><br>selos (a must)<br>charm (a must)<br>chain (good when the 2nd mob wants to flee)<br>hymn&nbsp;&nbsp;(You will get hit eventually)<br>speed song (good for finishing the final mob with weapons)<br><br><br>If you want to go pure instrumental. Just delete a weapon slot and set up a spell slot more and use single target dots.<br><br>When charmkiting have your drum in your hand at anytime when mobs are not fleeing (having speed is the best advantage ud get)<br><br>Hope this can be to use<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Cyrix<br>60 Bard<br>Test</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
